status: MARC21-007: Deterioration stage of motion picture
Level of deterioration of the motion picture film.

definition (en): No deterioration is apparent on either nitrate or non-nitrate motion picture film.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as suspicious odor.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as pungent odor.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as brownish, discoloration, fading, dusty.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as sticky.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as frothy, bubbles, blisters.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as congealed.
Deterioration of nitrate materials characterized as powder.
Deterioration of non-nitrate materials (safety film, etc.) characterized as detectable deterioration.
Deterioration of non-nitrate materials (safety film, etc.) characterized as advanced deterioration.
Deterioration of non-nitrate materials (safety film, etc.) characterized as disaster.
